gomodel:SYNGO_4028  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2C-F: RIM1/2 cDKO neurons showed more than 95% reduction in NPY-mCherry-labeled DCV fusion events upon stimulation compared to WT.\nFigure S3 C-G: The extrasynaptic events in RIM cDKO neurons lasted within 1 s (S3 E, indicated by a red bar), and were not detected as NPY-pHluorin-labeled fusion events.\nFigure S3 H: The total number of NPY-mCherry puncta was not altered between the genotypes.\nFigure S3 J-L: The loss of DCV fusion in RIM cDKO neurons was confirmed using BDNF-pHluorin as an independent reporter for neuromodulator release.\nFigure S6A-F: DCV fusion was strongly reduced in RIM1-deficient neurons (RIM1-/-, RIM2+/+ and RIM1-/-, RIM2+/-) and RIM2-deficient neurons heterozygous for RIM1 further denoting the role of RIM1 in the regulation of presynaptic dense-core vesicle exocytosis.. Experimental description: Homozygous double conditional RIM1αβ/RIM2αβγ mutant mice described previously (Kaeser et al., 2011, Kaeser et al., 2008) were used for timed mating of homozygous cDKO mice. All newborn (P1) RIM cDKO mice used for experiments were genotyped by PCR (Kaeser et al., 2011)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4028" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

